==English==

===Etymology===
The term may have arisen from the Indian word for a hired thug, ''[[goonda]]''.

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-uːn|-uːn]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A [[thug]], a usually muscular henchman with very little intelligence (also known as a 'Hired Goon'). The term ''goon'' rose to prominence in this context thanks to frequent usage in [[Popeye]].

